; Regression test for issue #1082: A change in precision used on an
; amount in-stream affects the balancing precision of following
; transactions.
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1082
;
; When a high-precision amount appeared in the journal, the commodity's
; global display precision was widened to match, causing two problems:
;   1. All amounts of that commodity were displayed at the inflated
;      precision (e.g. $10.00 displayed as $10.0000).
;   2. The widened precision tightened the is_zero() rounding tolerance
;      used during transaction balancing, causing previously-balanced
;      transactions to fail with "Transaction does not balance".
;

; The fix prevents precision migration once a commodity's precision has
; been established: high-precision amounts keep their own precision
; (BIGINT_USER_PREC) without infecting the commodity.


2024/01/01 Normal precision
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash      -$10.00

2024/01/02 High precision
    Expenses:Bar     $5.5555
    Assets:Cash      -$5.5555

2024/01/03 After precision change
    Expenses:Food    $3.00
    Assets:Cash      -$3.00

test bal
           $-18.5555  Assets:Cash
            $18.5555  Expenses
             $5.5555    Bar
              $13.00    Food
--------------------
                   0
end test

test reg
24-Jan-01 Normal precision      Expenses:Food                $10.00       $10.00
                                Assets:Cash                 $-10.00            0
24-Jan-02 High precision        Expenses:Bar                $5.5555      $5.5555
                                Assets:Cash                $-5.5555            0
24-Jan-03 After precision cha.. Expenses:Food                 $3.00        $3.00
                                Assets:Cash                  $-3.00            0
end test
